<subSubSection id="C3546563995D113CFD76F9AAFC16F913" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF136E8995D113CFD76F9AAFC16F913" blockId="92.[700,1229,1278,1741]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">DIAGNOSIS: The extraordinary, elongate pronotum (23:30) distinguishes the members of this species; the width across the eyes is greater than the width of the pronotum (23: 24); the frontal setal tuft and the metepisternal tuft are present.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF316660995C113DFE30F9ECFC1BF9A9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362808" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5362808" box="[415,936,1634,1655]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362808/files/figure.png" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" startId="93.[415,453,1634,1655]" targetBox="[123,1227,188,1612]" targetPageId="93">
